         <abstract>
            <p>In order to encourage corporations to disclose incipient problems promptly, the SEC requires them to file Report Form 8-K within 10 days after the close of any month in which certain problems arise. Among the 8-K disclosures, Item 10 (a) -- "Extraordinary Item Charges and Credits, Other Material Charges and Credits to Income of an Unusual Nature, and Material Provisions for Loss" -- is of special interest to investors because it is the only item that affects the income statement directly. Unfortunately, corporations' disclosure under Item 10 (a) is spotty and incomplete.</p>
          </abstract>
